nonsense_mediated_decay.label: nonsense mediated decay
nonsense_mediated_decay.definition: Coding transcript with a stop codon >50bp upstream of a splice site

non_stop_decay.label: non stop decay
non_stop_decay.definition: Coding transcript that has polyA features (including signal) without a preceeding stop codon in the CDS, i.e. a non-genomic polyA tail attached directly to the CDS without 3' UTR. These transcripts are subject to degradation

nontranslating_cds.label: nontranslating CDS
nontranslating_cds.definition: An imported 'protein-coding' gene that does not translate due to one or more unannotated stop codons

pirna.label: piRNA
pirna.definition: A small non coding RNA, part of a silencing system that prevents the spreading of selfish genetic elements

polymorphic_pseudogene.label: polymorphic pseudogene
polymorphic_pseudogene.definition: Disrupted protein-coding transcript at a locus that is disrupted in the reference genome but present as an intact protein-coding gene in other haplotypes

pre_mirna.label: pre miRNA
pre_mirna.definition: The 60-70 nt region remain after Drosha processing of the primary transcript, that folds back upon itself to form a hairpin structure

processed_pseudogene.label: processed pseudogene
processed_pseudogene.definition: Pseudogene derived via retrotransposition of the mRNA from a functional protein-coding gene

pseudogene.definition: Copy of a protein-coding gene containing disabling mutations and believed to not encode a stable and or functional protein

retained_intron.label: retained intron
